pokemon.name: Bulbasaur
pokemon.description: While it is young, it uses the nutrients that are stored in the seed on its back in order to grow.

pokemon.name: Ivysaur
pokemon.description: Exposure to sunlight adds to its strength. Sunlight also makes the bud on its back grow larger.

pokemon.name: Venusaur
pokemon.description: A bewitching aroma wafts from its flower. The fragrance becalms those engaged in a battle.

pokemon.name: Charmander
pokemon.description: From the time it is born, a flame burns at the tip of its tail. Its life would end if the flame were to go out.

pokemon.name: Charmeleon
pokemon.description: It has a barbaric nature. In battle, it whips its fiery tail around and slashes away with sharp claws.

pokemon.name: Charizard
pokemon.description: Its wings can carry this Pok√©mon close to an altitude of 4,600 feet. It's firery spit is hot enough to melt boulders

pokemon.name: Squirtle
pokemon.description: When it feels threatened, it draws its limbs inside its shell and sprays water from its mouth.

pokemon.name: Wartortle
pokemon.description: It cleverly controls its furry ears and tail to maintain its balance while swimming. If its shell has algae on it, that Wartortle is very old.

pokemon.name: Blastoise
pokemon.description: The rocket cannons on its shell fire jets of water capable of punching holes through thick steel.

pokemon.name: Caterpie
pokemon.description: For protection, it releases a horrible stench from the antenna on its head to drive away enemies. Its feet are tipped with suction pads that enable it to climb slopes and walls.

pokemon.name: Metapod
pokemon.description: It is waiting for the moment to evolve. At this stage, it can only harden, so it remains motionless to avoid attack.

pokemon.name: Butterfree
pokemon.description: It collects honey every day. It rubs honey onto the hairs on its legs to carry it back to its nest.

pokemon.name: Weedle
pokemon.description: Beware of the sharp stinger on its head. It hides in grass and bushes where it eats leaves.

pokemon.name: Kakuna
pokemon.description: Able to move only slightly. When endangered, it may stick out its stinger and poison its enemy.

pokemon.name: Beedrill
pokemon.description: It has three poisonous stingers on its forelegs and its tail. They are used to jab its enemy repeatedly.

pokemon.name: Pidgey
pokemon.description: Very docile. If attacked, it will often kick up sand to protect itself rather than fight back.

pokemon.name: Pidgeotto
pokemon.description: This Pok√©mon is full of vitality. It constantly flies around its large territory in search of prey.

pokemon.name: Pidgeot
pokemon.description: This Pok√©mon flies at Mach 2 speed, seeking prey. Its large talons are feared as wicked weapons.

pokemon.name: Rattata
pokemon.description: Will chew on anything with its fangs. If you see one, you can be certain that 40 more live in the area.

pokemon.name: Raticate
pokemon.description: Its hind feet are webbed. They act as flippers, so it can swim in rivers and hunt for prey.

pokemon.name: Spearow
pokemon.description: Inept at flying high. However, it can fly around very fast to protect its territory.

pokemon.name: Fearow
pokemon.description: A Pok√©mon that dates back many years. If it senses danger, it flies high and away, instantly.

pokemon.name: Ekans
pokemon.description: The older it gets, the longer it grows. At night, it wraps its long body around tree branches to rest.

pokemon.name: Arbok
pokemon.description: The frightening patterns on its belly have been studied. Six variations have been confirmed.

pokemon.name: Pikachu
pokemon.description: When Pikachu meet, they‚Äôll touch their tails together and exchange electricity through them as a form of greeting. Pikachu that can generate powerful electricity have cheek sacs that are extra soft and super stretchy.

pokemon.name: Raichu
pokemon.description: Its long tail serves as a ground to protect itself from its own high-voltage power. If its electric pouches run empty, it raises its tail to gather electricity from the atmosphere.

pokemon.name: Sandshrew
pokemon.description: It burrows into the ground to create its nest. If hard stones impede its tunneling, it uses its sharp claws to shatter them and then carries on digging.

pokemon.name: Sandslash
pokemon.description: The drier the area Sandslash lives in, the harder and smoother the Pok√©mon‚Äôs spikes will feel when touched.

pokemon.name: Nidoran ‚ôÄ (Female)
pokemon.description: A mild-mannered Pok√©mon that does not like to fight. Beware‚Äîits small horn secretes venom.

pokemon.name: Nidorina
pokemon.description: When resting deep in its burrow, its barbs always retract. This is proof that it is relaxed.

pokemon.name: Nidoqueen
pokemon.description: Tough scales cover the sturdy body of this Pok√©mon. It appears that the scales grow in cycles.

pokemon.name: Nidoran ‚ôÇ (Male)
pokemon.description: Its large ears are always kept upright. If it senses danger, it will attack with a poisonous sting.

pokemon.name: Nidorino
pokemon.description: Its horn contains venom. If it stabs an enemy with the horn, the impact makes the poison leak out.

pokemon.name: Nidoking
pokemon.description: Its steel-like hide adds to its powerful tackle. Its horns are so hard, they can pierce a diamond.

pokemon.name: Clefairy
pokemon.description: It is said that happiness will come to those who see a gathering of Clefairy dancing under a full moon.

pokemon.name: Clefable
pokemon.description: Their ears are sensitive enough to hear a pin drop from over a mile away, so they‚Äôre usually found in quiet places.

pokemon.name: Vulpix
pokemon.description: As each tail grows, its fur becomes more lustrous. When held, it feels slightly warm.

pokemon.name: Ninetales
pokemon.description: It is said to live 1,000 years, and each of its tails is loaded with supernatural powers.

pokemon.name: Jigglypuff
pokemon.description: By freely changing the wavelength of its voice, Jigglypuff sings a mysterious melody sure to make any listener sleepy.

pokemon.name: Wigglytuff
pokemon.description: The more air it takes in, the more it inflates. If opponents catch it in a bad mood, it will inflate itself to an enormous size to intimidate them.

pokemon.name: Zubat
pokemon.description: Emits ultrasonic cries while it flies. They act as a sonar used to check for objects in its way.

pokemon.name: Golbat
pokemon.description: It attacks in a stealthy manner, without warning. Its sharp fangs are used to bite and to suck blood.

pokemon.name: Oddish
pokemon.description: During the day, it stays in the cold underground to avoid the sun. It grows by bathing in moonlight.

pokemon.name: Gloom
pokemon.description: Its pistils exude an incredibly foul odor. The horrid stench can cause fainting at a distance of 1.25 miles. What appears to be drool is actually sweet honey. It is very sticky and clings stubbornly if touched.

pokemon.name: Vileplume
pokemon.description: The larger its petals, the more toxic pollen it contains. Its big head is heavy and hard to hold up.

pokemon.name: Paras
pokemon.description: Burrows under the ground to gnaw on tree roots. The mushrooms on its back absorb most of the nutrition.

pokemon.name: Parasect
pokemon.description: The bug host is drained of energy by the mushroom on its back. The mushroom appears to do all the thinking.

pokemon.name: Venonat
pokemon.description: Its large eyes act as radar. In a bright place, you can see that they are clusters of many tiny eyes.

pokemon.name: Venomoth
pokemon.description: The powdery scales on its wings are hard to remove from skin. They also contain poison that leaks out on contact.

pokemon.name: Diglett
pokemon.description: If a Diglett digs through a field, it leaves the soil perfectly tilled and ideal for planting crops.

pokemon.name: Dugtrio
pokemon.description: These Diglett triplets dig over 60 miles below sea level. No one knows what it‚Äôs like underground.

pokemon.name: Meowth
pokemon.description: It washes its face regularly to keep the coin on its forehead spotless. It loves to collect shiny things.

pokemon.name: Persian
pokemon.description: Its elegant and refined behavior clashes with that of the barbaric Perrserker. The relationship between the two is one of mutual disdain.

pokemon.name: Psyduck
pokemon.description: As Psyduck gets stressed out, its headache gets progressively worse. It uses intense psychic energy to overwhelm those around it.

pokemon.name: Golduck
pokemon.description: Old tales tell of Golduck punishing those that defiled its river. The guilty were dragged into the water and taken away.

pokemon.name: Mankey
pokemon.description: An agile Pok√©mon that lives in trees. It angers easily and will not hesitate to attack anything

pokemon.name: Primeape
pokemon.description: It stops being angry only when nobody else is around. To view this moment is very difficult.

pokemon.name: Growlithe
pokemon.description: Extremely loyal, it will fearlessly bark at any opponent to protect its own Trainer from harm.

pokemon.name: Arcanine
pokemon.description: A Pok√©mon that has long been admired for its beauty. It runs agilely as if on wings.

pokemon.name: Poliwag
pokemon.description: In rivers with fast-flowing water, this Pok√©mon will cling to a rock by using its thick lips, which act like a suction cup.

pokemon.name: Poliwhirl
pokemon.description: This Pok√©mon‚Äôs sweat is a slimy mucus. When captured, Poliwhirl can slither from its enemies‚Äô grasp and escape.

pokemon.name: Poliwrath
pokemon.description: Poliwrath is skilled at both swimming and martial arts. It uses its well-trained arms to dish out powerful punches.

pokemon.name: Abra
pokemon.description: Abra can teleport in its sleep. Apparently the more deeply Abra sleeps, the farther its teleportations go.

pokemon.name: Kadabra
pokemon.description: To prepare for evolution, Kadabra stores up psychic energy in the star on its forehead. Using its psychic power, Kadabra levitates as it sleeps. It uses its springy tail as a pillow.

pokemon.name: Alakazam
pokemon.description: Some say that Alakazam remembers everything that ever happens to it, from birth till death. It‚Äôs said that this Pok√©mon used its psychic powers to create the spoons it holds.

pokemon.name: Machop
pokemon.description: Always brimming with power, it passes time by lifting boulders. Doing so makes it even stronger.

pokemon.name: Machoke
pokemon.description: Its muscular body is so powerful, it must wear a power-save belt to be able to regulate its motions.

pokemon.name: Machamp
pokemon.description: It quickly swings its four arms to rock its opponents with ceaseless punches and chops from all angles.

pokemon.name: Bellsprout
pokemon.description: Prefers hot and humid places. It ensnares tiny bugs with its vines and devours them.

pokemon.name: Weepinbell
pokemon.description: When hungry, it swallows anything that moves. Its hapless prey is dissolved by strong acids.

pokemon.name: Victreebel
pokemon.description: Lures prey with the sweet aroma of honey. Swallowed whole, the prey is dissolved in a day, bones and all.

pokemon.name: Tentacool
pokemon.description: This Pok√©mon is mostly made of water. A Tentacool out in the ocean is very hard to spot, because its body blends in with the sea.

pokemon.name: Tentacruel
pokemon.description: When the red orbs on Tentacruel‚Äôs head glow brightly, watch out. The Pok√©mon is about to fire off a burst of ultrasonic waves.

pokemon.name: Geodude
pokemon.description: Commonly found near mountain trails and the like. If you step on one by accident, it gets angry.

pokemon.name: Graveler
pokemon.description: Often seen rolling down mountain trails. Obstacles are just things to roll straight over, not avoid.

pokemon.name: Golem
pokemon.description: Once it sheds its skin, its body turns tender and whitish. Its hide hardens when it‚Äôs exposed to air.

pokemon.name: Ponyta
pokemon.description: If you‚Äôve been accepted by Ponyta, its burning mane is mysteriously no longer hot to the touch.

pokemon.name: Rapidash
pokemon.description: This Pok√©mon can be seen galloping through fields at speeds of up to 150 mph, its fiery mane fluttering in the wind.

pokemon.name: Slowpoke
pokemon.description: When this Pok√©mon‚Äôs tail is soaked in water, sweetness seeps from it. Slowpoke uses this trait to lure in and fish up other Pok√©mon.

pokemon.name: Slowbro
pokemon.description: Slowpoke became Slowbro when a Shellder bit on to its tail. Sweet flavors seeping from the tail make the Shellder feel as if its life is a dream.

pokemon.name: Magnemite
pokemon.description: It subsists on electricity. As Magnemite flies, it emits electromagnetic waves from the units on each side of its body.

pokemon.name: Magneton
pokemon.description: This Pok√©mon is constantly putting out a powerful magnetic force. Most computers go haywire when a Magneton approaches.

pokemon.name: Farfetch'd
pokemon.description: They use a plant stalk as a weapon and several distinct styles of stalk fighting have been observed. In a dire situation, the stalk can also serve as food.

pokemon.name: Doduo
pokemon.description: Its short wings make flying difficult. Instead, this Pok√©mon runs at high speed on developed legs.

pokemon.name: Dodrio
pokemon.description: One of Doduo‚Äôs two heads splits to form a unique species. It runs close to 40 mph in prairies.

pokemon.name: Seel
pokemon.description: Loves freezing-cold conditions. Relishes swimming in a frigid climate of around 14 degrees Fahrenheit.

pokemon.name: Dewgong
pokemon.description: Its entire body is a snowy white. Unharmed by even intense cold, it swims powerfully in icy waters

pokemon.name: Grimer
pokemon.description: Made of congealed sludge. It smells too putrid to touch. Even weeds won‚Äôt grow in its path.

pokemon.name: Muk
pokemon.description: Smells so awful, it can cause fainting. Through degeneration of its nose, it lost its sense of smell.

pokemon.name: Shellder
pokemon.description: It swims facing backward by opening and closing its two-piece shell. It is surprisingly fast.

pokemon.name: Cloyster
pokemon.description: Once it slams its shell shut, it is impossible to open, even by those with superior strength.

pokemon.name: Gastly
pokemon.description: Born from gases, anyone would faint if engulfed by its gaseous body, which contains poison.

pokemon.name: Haunter
pokemon.description: If you get the feeling of being watched in darkness when nobody is around, Haunter is there. Its tongue is made of gas. If licked, its victim starts shaking constantly until death eventually comes.

pokemon.name: Gengar
pokemon.description: It is said to emerge from darkness to steal the lives of those who become lost in mountains.

pokemon.name: Onix
pokemon.description: As it digs through the ground, it absorbs many hard objects. This is what makes its body so solid.

pokemon.name: Drowzee
pokemon.description: If you sleep by it all the time, it will sometimes show you dreams it had eaten in the past.

pokemon.name: Hypno
pokemon.description: Avoid eye contact if you come across one. It will try to put you to sleep by using its pendulum.

pokemon.name: Krabby
pokemon.description: It can be found near the sea. The large pincers grow back if they are torn out of their sockets.

pokemon.name: Kingler
pokemon.description: Its large and hard pincer has 10,000-horsepower strength. However, being so big, it is unwieldy to move.

pokemon.name: Voltorb
pokemon.description: It is said to camouflage itself as a Pok√© Ball. It will self-destruct with very little stimulus.

pokemon.name: Electrode
pokemon.description: Stores electrical energy inside its body. Even the slightest shock could trigger a huge explosion.

pokemon.name: Exeggcute
pokemon.description: These Pok√©mon get nervous when they‚Äôre not in a group of six. The minute even one member of the group goes missing, Exeggcute become cowardly.

pokemon.name: Exeggutor
pokemon.description: Each of Exeggutor‚Äôs three heads is thinking different thoughts. The three don‚Äôt seem to be very interested in one another.

pokemon.name: Cubone
pokemon.description: When the memory of its departed mother brings it to tears, its cries echo mournfully within the skull it wears on its head.

pokemon.name: Marowak
pokemon.description: When this Pok√©mon evolved, the skull of its mother fused to it. Marowak‚Äôs temperament also turned vicious at the same time.

pokemon.name: Hitmonlee
pokemon.description: The legs freely contract and stretch. The stretchy legs allow it to hit a distant foe with a rising kick.

pokemon.name: Hitmonchan
pokemon.description: Its punches slice the air. They are launched at such high speed, even a slight graze could cause a burn.

pokemon.name: Lickitung
pokemon.description: Bug Pok√©mon are Lickitung‚Äôs main food source. This Pok√©mon paralyzes its prey with a lick from its long tongue, then swallows the prey whole.

pokemon.name: Koffing
pokemon.description: Its body is full of poisonous gas. It floats into garbage dumps, seeking out the fumes of raw, rotting trash.

pokemon.name: Weezing
pokemon.description: It mixes gases between its two bodies. It‚Äôs said that these Pok√©mon were seen all over the Galar region back in the day.

pokemon.name: Rhyhorn
pokemon.description: Strong, but not too bright, this Pok√©mon can shatter even a skyscraper with its charging tackles.

pokemon.name: Rhydon
pokemon.description: Protected by an armor-like hide, it is capable of living in molten lava of 3,600 degrees Fahrenheit.

pokemon.name: Chansey
pokemon.description: The egg Chansey carries is not only delicious but also packed with nutrition. It‚Äôs used as a high-class cooking ingredient.

pokemon.name: Tangela
pokemon.description: Hidden beneath a tangle of vines that grows nonstop even if the vines are torn off, this Pok√©mon‚Äôs true appearance remains a mystery.

pokemon.name: Kangaskhan
pokemon.description: There are records of a lost human child being raised by a childless Kangaskhan.

pokemon.name: Horsea
pokemon.description: They swim with dance-like motions and cause whirlpools to form. Horsea compete to see which of them can generate the biggest whirlpool.

pokemon.name: Seadra
pokemon.description: It‚Äôs the males that raise the offspring. While Seadra are raising young, the spines on their backs secrete thicker and stronger poison.

pokemon.name: Goldeen
pokemon.description: Its dorsal, pectoral, and tail fins wave elegantly in water. That is why it is known as the Water Dancer.

pokemon.name: Seaking
pokemon.description: In autumn, its body becomes more fatty in preparing to propose to a mate. It takes on beautiful colors.

pokemon.name: Staryu
pokemon.description: Fish Pok√©mon nibble at it, but Staryu isn‚Äôt bothered. Its body regenerates quickly, even if part of it is completely torn off.

pokemon.name: Starmie
pokemon.description: This Pok√©mon has an organ known as its core. The organ glows in seven colors when Starmie is unleashing its potent psychic powers.

pokemon.name: Mr. Mime
pokemon.description: It‚Äôs known for its top-notch pantomime skills. It protects itself from all sorts of attacks by emitting auras from its fingers to create walls.

pokemon.name: Scyther
pokemon.description: As Scyther fights more and more battles, its scythes become sharper and sharper. With a single slice, Scyther can fell a massive tree.

pokemon.name: Jynx
pokemon.description: Appears to move to a rhythm of its own, as if it were dancing. It wiggles its hips as it walks.

pokemon.name: Electabuzz
pokemon.description: If a major power outage occurs, it is certain that this Pok√©mon has eaten electricity at a power plant.

pokemon.name: Magmar
pokemon.description: Born in an active volcano. Its body is always cloaked in flames, so it looks like a big ball of fire.

pokemon.name: Pinsir
pokemon.description: This Pok√©mon clamps its pincers down on its prey and then either splits the prey in half or flings it away.

pokemon.name: Tauros
pokemon.description: When Tauros begins whipping itself with its tails, it‚Äôs a warning that the Pok√©mon is about to charge with astounding speed.

pokemon.name: Magikarp
pokemon.description: It is virtually worthless in terms of both power and speed. It is the most weak and pathetic Pok√©mon in the world.

pokemon.name: Gyarados
pokemon.description: It has an extremely aggressive nature. The Hyper Beam it shoots from its mouth totally incinerates all targets.

pokemon.name: Lapras
pokemon.description: A smart and kindhearted Pok√©mon. It uses its telepathic powers to communicate with humans.

pokemon.name: Ditto
pokemon.description: It can reconstitute its entire cellular structure to change into what it sees, but it returns to normal when it relaxes.

pokemon.name: Eevee
pokemon.description: Thanks to its unstable genetic makeup, this special Pok√©mon conceals many different possible evolutions.

pokemon.name: Vaporeon
pokemon.description: When Vaporeon‚Äôs fins begin to vibrate, it is a sign that rain will come within a few hours.

pokemon.name: Jolteon
pokemon.description: If it is angered or startled, the fur all over its body bristles like sharp needles that pierce foes.

pokemon.name: Flareon
pokemon.description: Once it has stored up enough heat, this Pok√©mon‚Äôs body temperature can reach up to 1,700 degrees Fahrenheit.

pokemon.name: Porygon
pokemon.description: State-of-the-art technology was used to create Porygon. It was the first artificial Pok√©mon to be created via computer programming.

pokemon.name: Omanyte
pokemon.description: An ancient Pok√©mon that was recovered from a fossil. It swam by cleverly twisting its 10 tentacles about.

pokemon.name: Omastar
pokemon.description: Its sharp beak rings its mouth. Its shell was too big for it to move freely, so it became extinct.

pokemon.name: Kabuto
pokemon.description: A Pok√©mon that was recovered from a fossil. It used the eyes on its back while hiding on the seafloor.

pokemon.name: Kabutops
pokemon.description: A slim and fast swimmer. It sliced its prey with its sharp sickles and drank the body fluids.

pokemon.name: Aerodactyl
pokemon.description: A savage Pok√©mon that died out in ancient times. It was resurrected using DNA taken from amber.

pokemon.name: Snorlax
pokemon.description: It is not satisfied unless it eats over 880 pounds of food every day. When it is done eating, it goes promptly to sleep.

pokemon.name: Articuno
pokemon.description: A legendary bird Pok√©mon. It freezes water that is contained in winter air and makes it snow.

pokemon.name: Zapdos
pokemon.description: This legendary bird Pok√©mon is said to appear when the sky turns dark and lightning showers down.

pokemon.name: Moltres
pokemon.description: A legendary bird Pok√©mon. As it flaps its flaming wings, even the night sky will turn red.

pokemon.name: Dratini
pokemon.description: Long thought to be a myth, this Pok√©mon‚Äôs existence was only recently confirmed by a fisherman who caught one.

pokemon.name: Dragonair
pokemon.description: According to a witness, its body was surrounded by a strange aura that gave it a mystical look.

pokemon.name: Dragonite
pokemon.description: It is said that this Pok√©mon lives somewhere in the sea and that it flies. However, these are only rumors.

pokemon.name: Mewtwo
pokemon.description: Mewtwo was artificially created from Mew's dna by scientists in a laboraty.

pokemon.name: Mew
pokemon.description: Mew is rarely observed as it has the power to transform into any Pok√©mon
